 Port Elizabeth - The Port Elizabeth office of the SA Weather Service says the nice drizzle overnight was good news for the gardens, but unfortunately, it did not do much for the Nelson Mandela Bay's catchment areas. "Port Elizabeth received between 5 mm at the airport and 12mm at Uitenhage," described Garth Sampson, SA Weather Service Client Liaison Officer (Eastern Cape Region). "The catchment area of the Langkloof received under 5 mm." He said that the highest rainfall figure was 28mm at Bisho. "Besides showers and thundershowers this afternoon, light falls are expected at times all the way till Friday."  Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 